snippet.textDisplay: So, typically, if you and your family cannot afford internet access, you probably don't live in an area where there's a Starbucks within walkable distance, and you probably don't have a laptop or smartphone. Some neighborhoods, towns, and cities don't get enough funding to even have libraries or schools with those resources. There are a lot of circumstances in which just "moving everyone's lawn" for 20 hours a day is not going to help. Maybe your neighbors don't have lawns. Maybe they do but are also too poor to hire someone to do their lawn. Maybe they do, but don't like your family, or the color of your skin, or the accent you speak in. Maybe it's dangerous for you to leave your neighborhood to offer commercial services in other more affluent neighborhoods. Maybe you can't be away from your home for long because you have to look after a sick relative, children, siblings, or what-have-you.
